full_description: GAMS (General Algebraic Modeling System) develops software for building and solving mathematical optimization models. For more than 35 years, researchers, engineers, and decision-makers in academia and industry have used GAMS to formulate complex problems in energy, economics, logistics, and engineering in a transparent and solver-agnostic way. GAMS provides a high-level modeling language, seamless access to a broad ecosystem of state-of-the-art solvers, and scalable execution from laptops to cloud infrastructure. With GAMSPy, GAMS brings optimization modeling directly into the Python ecosystem. GAMSPy allows users to define large-scale optimization models using familiar Python syntax while retaining the performance and rigor of mature optimization technology. By combining Pythonâ€™s flexibility with proven mathematical optimization, GAMS helps bridge the gap between data science, research, and real-world decision support.
